April 2017 in pictures

I didn't seem to take that many photos in April. I was in Frankfurt the entire month and was busy working away and enjoying the couple of long weekends. Nevertheless, I did take few photos, so here they are - enjoy!

100 things I’ve learnt in Frankfurt

Due to me being a complete geek with numbers (I get it off my mum!) and using one of my favourite websites - Wolfram|Alpha - I've worked out that today is my 100th day in Frankfurt. And what better way to celebrate than with a fun blog post around the number 100. Here are the 100 things… Continue reading 100 things I’ve learnt in Frankfurt

Nintendo, a new WG… and did I mention Nintendo?

Guten Abend and good evening! I am now just about half way into Week 7 of my Frankfurt life, and I am still loving every single minute of it - even the working bit, believe it or not!
